1
00:00:00,443 --> 00:00:02,969
Interviewer: Where did you
go once you left this place?

2
00:00:02,994 --> 00:00:05,026
I left this place and
he took me to the judge

3
00:00:05,130 --> 00:00:08,750
He witnessed my flogging
punishment, and gave me a receipt

4
00:00:08,906 --> 00:00:10,677
He said, Take him
and give him his ID

5
00:00:11,693 --> 00:00:16,744
There at the headquarters, at the center
that used to be the old police station

6
00:00:17,031 --> 00:00:18,672
That’s where the IDs were

7
00:00:19,063 --> 00:00:22,448
I went and gave him the receipt—he
pulled out my ID and handed it to me

8
00:00:22,578 --> 00:00:23,906
I took it and went home

9
00:00:24,792 --> 00:00:28,203
Interviewer: Do you still have the receipt?
Witness: Yes, it’s at home

10
00:00:29,479 --> 00:00:34,479
Interviewer: The jailer
took you to interrogation

11
00:00:34,504 --> 00:00:36,458
And from the
interrogation to there

12
00:00:37,188 --> 00:00:38,021
Interviewer: Shall we go out?

13
00:00:38,046 --> 00:00:38,958
Let’s go

14
00:01:08,651 --> 00:01:09,667
Interviewer: Was the ISIS
member walking with you here then?

15
00:01:09,692 --> 00:01:13,495
Yes, he was walking with me and brought
me in to the investigative judge here

16
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:14,537
Interviewer: After
he let you out?

17
00:01:14,562 --> 00:01:17,349
After he let me out, I
walked with him normally

18
00:01:17,662 --> 00:01:20,709
I went to pick up the ID from
the center and then home

19
00:01:20,839 --> 00:01:22,115
Interviewer: Were you hurt?

20
00:01:22,401 --> 00:01:23,521
How could I not be hurt!?

21
00:01:23,546 --> 00:01:27,682
I even had trouble
putting on my sweater

22
00:01:28,282 --> 00:01:32,865
When I got home I took the sweater off, for
ten days I couldn’t wear anything on top

23
00:01:34,558 --> 00:01:36,068
Ten days, I couldn’t wear it

24
00:01:36,954 --> 00:01:38,750
Because of the pain
the torture left in my back

25
00:01:39,506 --> 00:01:42,839
Interviewer: Did it leave a
mark on your body until now?

26
00:01:42,864 --> 00:01:45,547
No, no mark remains now

27
00:01:45,938 --> 00:01:48,282
That detention was
seven years ago

28
00:01:49,740 --> 00:01:55,105
The flogging didn’t leave a
deep pit or anything like that

29
00:01:57,084 --> 00:01:59,688
The effect was like someone who had
swum under the sun and got sunburned

30
00:02:00,547 --> 00:02:02,240
And he can’t sleep on his back

31
00:02:02,474 --> 00:02:03,490
The same situation

32
00:02:03,515 --> 00:02:05,209
But this was
flogging, not the sun

33
00:02:40,573 --> 00:02:43,698
I left, took my ID,
and then went home

34
00:02:44,349 --> 00:02:46,381
You can’t work
or do anything else

35
00:02:46,849 --> 00:02:50,704
Ten days I slept on my face

36
00:02:51,797 --> 00:02:52,969
Because of the pain in my back

37
00:02:53,723 --> 00:02:54,505
Interviewer: Did you
leave through this door?

38
00:02:54,531 --> 00:02:56,042
Yes, they took me
out through this door

39
00:02:57,031 --> 00:02:59,323
From here they took
me to the main street

40
00:02:59,348 --> 00:03:02,500
And to the center, that center I told you
about across from the Prophet Jirjis Mosque

41
00:03:03,516 --> 00:03:05,156
It was an old police station

42
00:03:05,599 --> 00:03:07,500
They were based there

43
00:03:08,151 --> 00:03:11,484
I got my ID and left
